# Enforce LF line endings in the repository for all text files.
#
# Why: this repo is developed across Windows, WSL, macOS and Linux. Without this,
# a Windows checkout (core.autocrlf=true) writes CRLF to the working tree while the
# committed blobs are LF, and a Linux/WSL git then reports the ENTIRE tree as modified
# (the "whole tree modified, zero untracked files" trap). Pinning eol=lf makes the
# committed form canonical and keeps every platform consistent. Git auto-detects
# binary content and leaves it untouched.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Scripts that must stay LF regardless of platform.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Common binary assets — never apply line-ending conversion (defensive; the repo is
# currently all-text, these guard future additions).
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.pdf  binary
*.zip  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf  binary
*.otf  binary
